I’d like to talk about a time when I saw a lunar eclipse, which was a really memorable experience for me.

It happened about two years ago in Ho Chi Minh City. I found out about this event through online news and social media a few days in advance, so I had time to plan to watch it with my friends.

On that day, we went to a park in the evening and found a good spot to sit and wait. We brought some snacks and drinks, so we could relax and chat while waiting for the eclipse to start. I remember feeling quite excited because it was the first time I had ever seen a lunar eclipse in real life.

As it got darker, we started to see the shadow slowly cover the moon. It was really fascinating to watch the bright moon gradually turn dark. Many people around us were taking photos and videos, and I did the same to keep it as a memory.

Overall, I felt amazed and a bit surprised by how beautiful the scene was. It made me realize how interesting nature can be, and I hope I will have a chance to see more events like this in the future.
